1
00:00:01,650 --> 00:00:10,800
TOHO CORPORATION

2
00:00:53,940 --> 00:00:58,090
Some mornings, I wake up crying
without knowing why.

3
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:01,440
That's when everything happens
now and again.

4
00:01:02,060 --> 00:01:06,540
Whatever that dream was I had,
I can never remember it.

5
00:01:06,540 --> 00:01:09,550
- But...
- But...

6
00:01:09,550 --> 00:01:12,190
the only thing that
does last when I wake up

7
00:01:12,190 --> 00:01:14,190
is a sense of loss,

8
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:17,190
which lingers for a long time afterwards.

9
00:01:23,850 --> 00:01:26,700
I'm always searching for something

10
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:28,700
or someone.

11
00:01:28,750 --> 00:01:31,090
Mitsuha: I've been consumed by this feeling...

12
00:01:31,920 --> 00:01:34,090
ever since that day.

13
00:01:35,040 --> 00:01:38,910
Taki: The day... a star fell.

14
00:01:38,910 --> 00:01:40,460
It was almost like...

15
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:42,450
-like seeing something out of a dream.

16
00:01:43,760 --> 00:01:46,450
Nothing more or less...

17
00:01:46,460 --> 00:01:48,400
- than a breathtaking view.
- than a breathtaking view.

18
00:01:48,970 --> 00:01:54,430
Ah, if only our voices speak at night

19
00:01:54,430 --> 00:01:58,100
could ever reach the very
edge of this world

20
00:01:58,100 --> 00:01:59,610
and of time

21
00:01:59,910 --> 00:02:04,790
instead of fading into air and dust.

22
00:02:04,790 --> 00:02:07,840
Then what will the words, could it ever be

23
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:10,540
farthest words from "probably"?

24
00:02:10,550 --> 00:02:13,050
Let's make a promise that will never fade.

25
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:16,830
Let's say it together on
the count of three, oh.

26
00:02:27,750 --> 00:02:30,960
Ah, I'm told that some part of
every wish will be heard,

27
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:33,730
but lately I've lost sight of
the truth in those words.

28
00:02:33,730 --> 00:02:36,980
I can't even remember when
I gave up believing.

29
00:02:36,980 --> 00:02:38,550
What could have been the reason?

30
00:02:38,550 --> 00:02:41,870
Ah, the very moment that the rain will stop

31
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:44,410
in the place rainbow born and dies.

32
00:02:44,410 --> 00:02:46,350
And where the end of this life lies,

33
00:02:46,350 --> 00:02:50,020
I've always been insisting there was
something that I've longing for.

34
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:59,990
One day we'll reach to emotions
unexplored, unprecedented.

35
00:02:59,990 --> 00:03:04,720
We'll high-five love we've yet to
discover and give a kiss to time.

36
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:07,380
The five dimensions keeps on teasing me,

37
00:03:07,380 --> 00:03:10,440
but I will keep on looking at you, dear.

38
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:14,770
Let's make a sign for when we
say "nice to meet you" again.

39
00:03:16,290 --> 00:03:17,660
I'm on my way to you,

40
00:03:17,660 --> 00:03:20,610
chasing after your name.

41
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,140
Taki...

42
00:03:46,140 --> 00:03:47,890
Taki.

43
00:03:47,890 --> 00:03:49,900
Taki!

44
00:03:50,660 --> 00:03:52,270
Don't you remember?

45
00:03:55,290 --> 00:03:58,330
My name is...

46
00:03:58,330 --> 00:03:59,020
Mitsuha!

47
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:38,010
Sis, what are you... doing?

48
00:04:38,030 --> 00:04:41,390
Whoa, they're so realistic-feeling...

49
00:04:42,200 --> 00:04:43,110
"Sis"?

50
00:04:43,110 --> 00:04:44,220
Me?

51
00:04:44,220 --> 00:04:45,880
Are you still asleep?

52
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:49,010
Breakfast time, hurry up!

53
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,050
Huh?

54
00:05:10,050 --> 00:05:11,420
Wha-?

55
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:13,260
WHAAAT?!

56
00:05:19,930 --> 00:05:22,490
Do you wanna have any of
last night's fish, grandma?

57
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:24,190
You can eat it.

58
00:05:24,710 --> 00:05:26,210
- Mornin'!
- Mornin'!

59
00:05:26,210 --> 00:05:28,330
Lazy butt, you're so slow!

60
00:05:28,330 --> 00:05:30,540
I'll fix breakfast tomorrow.

61
