77
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:24,070
"Position of Comet Tiamat"

78
00:06:24,070 --> 00:06:25,070
"Closest on October 4th"

79
00:06:41,430 --> 00:06:43,120
- We're leaving!
- We're leaving!

80
00:06:46,390 --> 00:06:50,550
Yotsuha: I can't wait 'til the festival!
It's gonna be so much fun!

81
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:05,570
Study hard, sis!

82
00:07:08,400 --> 00:07:09,860
Ah!

83
00:07:10,850 --> 00:07:12,420
Mitsuha!

84
00:07:12,420 --> 00:07:14,370
Good mornin', Saya! Mornin', Teshi!

85
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:17,040
- Mornin'!
- Come on, would you get off already?

86
00:07:17,040 --> 00:07:19,160
- What for, meanie?
- 'Cause you're heavy.

87
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:22,360
- Hey, that's rude!
- Y'know, I gotta say. You two make a great couple.

88
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:24,050
- No, we don't!
- No, we don't!

89
00:07:25,730 --> 00:07:28,930
Oh, I see you actually
bothered to do your hair today.

90
00:07:28,930 --> 00:07:32,780
-Wait, what?
-Oh, yeah. What happened?
Did your grandma exorcise all your demons?

91
00:07:32,780 --> 00:07:36,200
- Exorcise?
- Somethin' totally possessed your body!

92
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:39,190
Would you just give it a rest
with all this occult nonsense?

93
00:07:39,190 --> 00:07:43,660
- Mitsuha's gotta be feelin'
stressed enough as it is, right?
- What are you guys talking about?

94
00:07:43,660 --> 00:07:45,660
Are you feelin' okay?

95
00:07:46,910 --> 00:07:53,710
And above all, restoring the town's fiscal health
so we can continue our revitalization project.

96
00:07:53,710 --> 00:07:59,610
It's only when all these things are achieved
that we can create a safe and secure community.

97
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:04,900
- As the incumbent, my administration...
- Miyamizu's gonna get another term anyway.

98
00:08:04,900 --> 00:08:08,270
I hear he's been dullin' out the pork.
Just between us.

99
00:08:08,270 --> 00:08:11,450
- Hey, Miyamizu.
- Mornin'.

100
00:08:11,450 --> 00:08:15,650
Looks like the mayor and the
contractor's kid are pretty cozy, too.

101
00:08:15,650 --> 00:08:19,790
-To improve the quality of
life of each and every resident.

102
00:08:20,840 --> 00:08:22,540
- Mitsuha!
- [Gasp]

103
00:08:22,670 --> 00:08:25,140
Stand up straight when you're walking!

104
00:08:25,550 --> 00:08:27,510
Oh, he's tough on his family.

105
00:08:27,510 --> 00:08:28,970
Well, that's the mayor for ya.

106
00:08:28,970 --> 00:08:31,420
- Awkward.
- Sucks to be her.

107
00:08:32,420 --> 00:08:34,140
Mitsuha!

108
00:08:34,830 --> 00:08:36,480
In front of everyone.

109
00:08:39,900 --> 00:08:41,180
"Who are you?"

110
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:51,110
"Tasokare" [Twilight]

111
00:08:50,450 --> 00:08:54,010
"Two light." That's the
origin of the word twilight.

112
00:08:54,010 --> 00:08:56,770
I'm sure everyone here knows that word.

113
00:08:56,770 --> 00:09:00,220
It's dusk, a time when
it's neither day nor night.

114
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:02,690
When the border between worlds blur,

115
00:09:02,690 --> 00:09:05,670
and one might encounter
something not human.

116
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:10,350
Another older term for it is dusk light.

117
00:09:10,350 --> 00:09:13,510
Some people also call it "golden hour".

118
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:16,210
"Karetaso/Kawatare = Who is that?"

119
00:09:13,510 --> 00:09:16,370
-What about "magic hour"?
It's something my grandma says.

120
00:09:16,370 --> 00:09:20,140
-Well, golden hour and magic
hour are technically the same,

121
00:09:20,140 --> 00:09:22,860
but it's a term that
mostly photographers use.

122
00:09:22,860 --> 00:09:27,220
"Who are you?"

123
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:26,780
- Well, she does take a lot of pictures.
- [CLASS Laughing]

124
00:09:28,090 --> 00:09:29,980
-Okay, next...

125
00:09:29,980 --> 00:09:32,330
- Miyamizu!
- Uh, yes?

126
00:09:32,330 --> 00:09:35,700
Well, I can see that you
remember your own name today.

127
00:09:35,700 --> 00:09:37,700
[Laughing]

128
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,660
Sayaka: You... don't remember?
Mitsuha: Uh-uh...

129
00:09:41,660 --> 00:09:45,880
Well, believe it or not, you forgot where
your own desk and locker were yesterday.

130
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:49,980
Plus, you had the worst case of bedhead,
and you didn't have your ribbon on, either!

131
00:09:52,860 --> 00:09:54,540
What?! No way!

132
00:09:54,540 --> 00:09:57,190
Yeah, it was like you
had amnesia or somethin'.

133
00:09:57,190 --> 00:10:01,840
Now that you mention it, I do feel like
I've been havin' weird dreams lately.

134
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:05,860
Like a dream about someone else's life?

135
00:10:06,020 --> 00:10:08,120
It's all so fuzzy.

136
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:10,660
Wait a sec, I've got it...

137
00:10:10,660 --> 00:10:12,420
It's memories from a previous life,

138
00:10:12,420 --> 00:10:16,250
or maybe your subconscious linked to the
Everett interpretation of the multiverse!

139
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:17,570
Keep your full mouth shut!

140
00:10:17,570 --> 00:10:22,390
Wait a minute! Teshi, don't tell me you
were the one who wrote in my noteboo... k.

141
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:24,510
Forget it.

142
00:10:25,170 --> 00:10:29,500
But you really were actin' just a
little funny yesterday, Mitsuha.

143
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:31,730
You been feelin' okay?

144
00:10:32,450 --> 00:10:35,450
That's what's weird. I feel fine.

145
00:10:35,580 --> 00:10:39,600
Maybe it's from stress. You know, you've
got that ritual comin' up soon, don'tcha?

146
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,800
Ugh, don't remind me!

147
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:46,380
I can't stand this place anymore!
It's too small and town-ey.

148
00:10:46,380 --> 00:10:50,870
I wanna graduate already and
go to Tokyo as soon as I can!

149
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:56,130
-Can't say I blame you. There really
is nothin' at all in this town.

150
00:10:57,100 --> 00:11:01,660
-There's only one train that stops here every two
hours -and all the stores close at nine o' clock.

151
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:03,770
No bookstores, no dentists,

152
00:11:03,490 --> 00:11:05,940
"Mother's" "Cat's Eye Pub"

153
00:11:03,770 --> 00:11:06,140
but two cocktail lounges
for whatever reason.

154
00:11:06,140 --> 00:11:08,620
- No jobs in town.
- No one date-able.

155
00:11:08,620 --> 00:11:11,230
Even the days are too short.

156
00:11:12,340 --> 00:11:13,470
You know what?!

157
00:11:13,470 --> 00:11:15,150
- No, what?
- No, what?

158
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:18,500
Forget that stuff.
Why don't we go to a café?

159
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:19,960
- A café?
- Really?

160
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,260
- Where?!
- Where?!

161
00:11:25,820 --> 00:11:26,800
Hello, kids!

162
00:11:26,800 --> 00:11:28,160
- Hi, there!
- Evenin', ma'am!

163
00:11:33,050 --> 00:11:36,740
- How is this a café?
- Like this town's got a café.

164
00:11:37,050 --> 00:11:39,680
Mitsuha just went straight home.

165
00:11:40,670 --> 00:11:45,480
- Things have gotta be really
rough for her right now.
- She's on center stage and all.

166
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:46,480
Yeah...

167
00:11:49,810 --> 00:11:52,440
- Hey, Teshi...
- Hm?

168
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:55,900
What are you gonna do after
you graduate high school?

169
00:11:55,900 --> 00:11:58,880
Where'd that come from?
You talkin' about the future?

170
00:11:58,880 --> 00:12:00,370
Mh-hm.

171
00:12:00,660 --> 00:12:05,950
I dunno. I think I'll probably just end up
livin' in this town, y'know. Same as ever.

172
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:23,940
I wanna do what you're doin'.

173
00:12:23,940 --> 00:12:26,850
It's still too soon for you to
try, Yotsuha.

174
00:12:26,850 --> 00:12:29,380
Listen to the thread's voice.

175
00:12:29,380 --> 00:12:35,880
When you twine it round and round like this, feelings
will start flowing between you and the thread.

176
00:12:36,710 --> 00:12:40,950
- It's not like threads talk...
- She's telling you to focus.

177
00:12:40,950 --> 00:12:46,570
Etched within our braided cords is a
thousand years' worth of Itomori's history.

178
00:12:46,570 --> 00:12:50,620
Listen. Somethin' happened
two hundred years ago...

179
00:12:50,620 --> 00:12:52,040
Here she goes.

180
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:59,170
The bathroom of sandal maker Mayugoro Yamazaki
caught on fire and this whole area burned down.

181
00:12:59,270 --> 00:13:02,650
The shrine and old
documents were destroyed.

182
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:06,070
- This is known as...
- Mayugoro's Great Fire.

183
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:10,600
They named the fire after him?!
I feel bad for Mayugoro.

184
00:13:11,390 --> 00:13:15,150
The meaning behind our festivals
was lost because of that.

185
00:13:15,150 --> 00:13:17,740
Only the surface was left.

186
00:13:17,740 --> 00:13:22,040
But even if those words are
gone, those words shouldn't fade.

187
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:26,530
That's the Miyamizu shrine's duty.
Our important task.

188
00:13:27,220 --> 00:13:28,830
Ugh...

189
00:13:28,830 --> 00:13:32,660
Despite all that, that son-in-law of mine!

190
00:13:32,660 --> 00:13:38,360
Abandoning the Shinto priesthood and leaving
this house were bad enough, but politics?!

191
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:41,010
Oh, he's hopeless!

192
00:13:41,460 --> 00:13:43,540
-Have another, mister foreman.

193
00:13:46,570 --> 00:13:50,390
- I'll be counting on your
help again for this election.
- Leave it to me.

194
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:54,320
You'll get the votes from the
Kadoiri and Sakagami Districts, guaranteed.

195
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:57,960
- How's the datin' scene?
- It ain't easy, that's for sure.

196
00:13:59,350 --> 00:14:03,520
- Smells like corruption in there.
- What are you talkin' about?

197
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:07,280
- We're gonna need two
or three more bottles.
- Yes, dear.

198
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:10,310
Katsuhiko, you're gonna help
out at the site this weekend.

199
00:14:10,310 --> 00:14:13,520
- We'll be usin' explosives,
so you better study up.
- Grngh.

200
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:14,580
What was that?!

201
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:16,580
Got it!

202
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:31,930
Guess we both can't stand things here.

203
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:53,180
Is that Yotsuha? She's all grown up.

204
00:14:53,180 --> 00:14:55,900
They're lookers, alright.
Just like their mother.

205
00:14:57,550 --> 00:15:00,520
- Heya!
- Hey.

206
00:15:32,330 --> 00:15:34,700
World's oldest kind of sake,

207
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:40,660
but chewin' on rice, spittin' it out, and then
lettin' it ferment naturally, it becomes alcohol.

208
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:42,660
Kuchikamizake.

209
00:15:42,790 --> 00:15:45,720
Do the gods really appreciate that.
The way it's ma-

210
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:47,910
Yeah, of course they do!

211
00:15:49,660 --> 00:15:53,010
Hey, check it out. It's Miyamizu.

212
00:15:57,500 --> 00:16:04,030
-Ugh! I'd never do that!
-And in front of everybody!
Embarrassing, right?

213
00:16:17,550 --> 00:16:19,870
You should try to cheer up, sis.

214
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:23,010
Who cares if a few of the kids
from your school saw that?

215
00:16:23,010 --> 00:16:25,940
It must be nice for you
not being a teenager.

216
00:16:26,410 --> 00:16:31,000
Hey, I know! You should just sell
Kuchikamizake and move to Tokyo!

217
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:35,860
I bet you could sell it with all sorts of
stuff like photos and making-of videos.

218
00:16:35,860 --> 00:16:41,910
Oh, and then you can call it "Shrine
Maiden's Sake"! You'll make buttloads!

219
00:16:41,890 --> 00:16:43,890
"Shrine Maiden's Sake"

220
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:48,280
I can't! There are liquor laws!

221
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:50,470
That's what you have a problem with?

222
00:16:56,430 --> 00:17:01,320
I hate this town! I hate this life, too!

223
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:08,690
Please make me a handsome
Tokyo boy in my next life!

224
00:17:10,140 --> 00:17:12,770
Yotsuha: What a jackass.

225
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:41,820
Ow...

226
00:17:54,290 --> 00:17:55,480
Where...?

227
00:17:56,150 --> 00:17:57,260
Huh?

228
00:18:03,520 --> 00:18:04,840
Hmm?

229
00:18:06,610 --> 00:18:09,020
Something's... there...

230
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:15,040
Aaaah!

231
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:23,810
Eh!

232
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:25,840
Taki's Father: Taki, you up?

233
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:31,780
It was your turn to cook breakfast,
wasn't it? Did you sleep in?

234
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:33,690
I'm sorry.

235
00:18:34,020 --> 00:18:36,040
Ugh, I'm heading out.

236
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:39,110
- Finish the miso.
- Uh, okay...

237
00:18:39,110 --> 00:18:42,640
Make sure you go to school,
even if you're late. Seeya.

238
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:45,550
H-have a nice day.

239
00:18:56,140 --> 00:18:57,860
What a strange dream...

240
