485
00:36:30,230 --> 00:36:37,160
You'll offer it at the foot of the shrine
god's relic. After all, it is half of you.

486
00:36:38,830 --> 00:36:41,670
Half... of Mitsuha.

487
00:36:58,970 --> 00:37:02,010
Wow, it's already magic hour!

488
00:37:02,090 --> 00:37:04,010
Magic hour?

489
00:37:13,870 --> 00:37:19,730
- Oh, yeah! Maybe I can see the comet!
- Huh? The comet?

490
00:37:20,320 --> 00:37:23,490
Oh, Mitsuha...

491
00:37:23,490 --> 00:37:26,990
you're dreaming right now, aren't you?

492
00:37:38,050 --> 00:37:40,950
I'm crying? But why?

493
00:37:43,010 --> 00:37:45,510
"I'm almost there. Looking forward to it!"

494
00:37:46,130 --> 00:37:49,820
Ms. Okudera? She's almost where?

495
00:37:51,150 --> 00:37:54,160
Oh, Mitsuha. What did you do?

496
00:37:54,390 --> 00:37:55,480
Date?!

497
00:38:03,120 --> 00:38:06,300
Mitsuha: "Tomorrow's your Tokyo date with Ms.
Okudera."

498
00:38:06,320 --> 00:38:09,090
"Meet up at the station at 10:30!"

499
00:38:10,480 --> 00:38:14,020
Well, that's what I had planned, but...

500
00:38:27,260 --> 00:38:29,790
- Hi, Taki.
- Huh? Agh!

501
00:38:30,610 --> 00:38:35,620
- Wait long?
- Yeah. Aah-no! Uh...

502
00:38:43,860 --> 00:38:48,110
- I just got here.
- Thank goodness. Let's go!

503
00:38:49,690 --> 00:38:54,090
Must be nice.
They've probably met up about now.

504
00:38:57,520 --> 00:38:59,880
Huh?

505
00:39:02,230 --> 00:39:04,740
Why am I...?

506
00:39:05,020 --> 00:39:07,070
Why...?

507
00:39:12,400 --> 00:39:19,700
"It was a date I wanted to go on, but if it so happens that
you end up goin', you better be grateful and enjoy it!"

508
00:39:20,380 --> 00:39:27,780
This is nice! It's my first time here.
So, is this one of your usual go-to spots?

509
00:39:24,990 --> 00:39:30,270
Mitsuha: "At any rate, I bet you've
never even been on a single date."

510
00:39:27,780 --> 00:39:30,270
No way, it's too expensive!

511
00:39:31,250 --> 00:39:33,230
I don't know what to say to her.

512
00:39:33,230 --> 00:39:37,900
"That's why I've handpicked some links
below to help you out, ya wallflower!"

513
00:39:37,900 --> 00:39:38,940
For real?

514
00:39:39,530 --> 00:39:40,370
"You, too, can get a girlfriend!"

515
00:39:42,540 --> 00:39:45,830
"Despite social anxiety, I got a girl!"
"The dos and don'ts of texting!"

516
00:39:46,230 --> 00:39:48,370
She's making fun of me!

517
00:39:48,380 --> 00:39:52,390
"Photo Exhibition: Nostalgia"

518
00:40:17,170 --> 00:40:18,960
You know something, Taki?

519
00:40:19,530 --> 00:40:24,230
Today, you're...
you're like a different person.

520
00:40:32,450 --> 00:40:37,810
Ms. Okudera. You getting hungry?
We could get dinner.

521
00:40:38,090 --> 00:40:43,630
- Uh... let's call it a day.
- U-uh... Alright.

522
00:40:44,060 --> 00:40:48,470
- I could be wrong, and I'm sorry if I am...
- About?

523
00:40:48,590 --> 00:40:52,410
But you used to have a
little crush on me, am I right?

524
00:40:53,710 --> 00:40:57,070
But right now,
there's someone else you like, huh?

525
00:40:57,130 --> 00:41:01,760
- N-n-no! U-uh-it's not that...
- Really?

526
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:06,190
- There's no one. It's not like that.
- Are you sure about that?

527
00:41:07,340 --> 00:41:11,040
Well, thanks for today. See you at work!

528
00:41:25,740 --> 00:41:27,750
Taki: By the time the date's over,

529
00:41:27,750 --> 00:41:31,190
-you should be able to
see the comet in the sky.
-"...you should be able to
see the comet in the sky."

530
00:41:34,020 --> 00:41:37,710
What does she mean? Weirdo.

531
00:42:05,090 --> 00:42:06,130
-Oh.

532
00:42:06,130 --> 00:42:07,820
Mitsuha: It's you, Teshi.

533
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:12,520
No. I just didn't feel like
goin', that's all. I'm fine.

534
00:42:13,490 --> 00:42:16,610
What? The festival?

535
00:42:16,610 --> 00:42:18,440
Ah...

536
00:42:18,440 --> 00:42:23,250
Oh yeah, the comet.
It'll be at its brightest today, right?

537
00:42:23,550 --> 00:42:26,490
Okay, got it. Seeya later!

538
00:42:30,030 --> 00:42:33,600
You're just looking forward to seeing
Mitsuha in a yukata, aren'tcha?

539
00:42:33,600 --> 00:42:35,340
I- I am not!

540
00:42:35,340 --> 00:42:37,340
I mean, it didn't even cross my mind.

541
00:42:38,380 --> 00:42:43,730
- Y'know, she sounded kinda down when I talked to her.
- Maybe she just didn't want a call from ya.

542
00:42:43,730 --> 00:42:45,120
It's not funny!

543
00:42:45,120 --> 00:42:47,450
- Sorry to keep ya.
- Oh, she's here!
- You're late!

544
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:50,060
- [Gasp]
- [Gasp]

545
00:42:50,060 --> 00:42:54,110
- Mitsuha, what happened to-?
- [Gasp]

546
00:42:54,110 --> 00:42:56,070
-Your hair!

547
00:42:56,070 --> 00:42:59,200
I guess... it's weird.

548
00:43:07,710 --> 00:43:11,120
You think it's gotta do with some guy.
Like, he broke her heart?

549
00:43:11,120 --> 00:43:14,480
Guys always just assume that
it has to do with a boy.

550
00:43:14,480 --> 00:43:21,370
- She said she felt like cuttin' it.
- Ya sure about that? You really think she
felt like cuttin' off that much of it?

551
00:43:21,370 --> 00:43:24,750
Hey guys, I can see it!

552
00:43:41,750 --> 00:43:45,400
- Whoa, ho-ho!
- Whoa...
- Ah.

553
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:51,590
Huh?

554
00:44:02,160 --> 00:44:07,780
Phone: "The number you are trying to reach is currently
outside the cellular network or has been turned off due-"

555
00:44:10,410 --> 00:44:15,320
Taki: I'll just have to tell her how lousy
the date ended up the next time we switch.

556
00:44:15,320 --> 00:44:17,630
That's what I thought.

557
00:44:17,630 --> 00:44:20,430
But, for some reason,

558
00:44:20,430 --> 00:44:24,630
the switches Mitsuha and I had
been going through until now...

559
00:44:24,630 --> 00:44:28,400
they never happened again.

560
00:45:01,070 --> 00:45:04,080
"Mountains in Gifu Prefecture"

561
00:45:14,900 --> 00:45:16,530
"Hida Mountains"

562
00:46:19,270 --> 00:46:20,560
Wha-

563
00:46:20,560 --> 00:46:21,940
What are-

564
00:46:21,940 --> 00:46:24,530
What are you doing here?

565
00:46:26,690 --> 00:46:29,580
Okudera: Tsukasa told me about it, so here I am.

566
00:46:32,790 --> 00:46:37,900
I asked for two things: to cover my shift
and to back up my alibi if my dad asked.

567
00:46:37,900 --> 00:46:39,980
Relax, Takagi's gonna take your shift.

568
00:46:39,980 --> 00:46:41,400
Takagi: Gotch'a covered!

569
00:46:41,400 --> 00:46:43,350
But you owe me dinner.

570
00:46:43,510 --> 00:46:46,600
- So, you're all in on it...
- You've got everyone worried about you.

571
00:46:46,600 --> 00:46:50,700
- Huh?
- We can't ignore this! What if somebody's
trying to pull one over on you?

572
00:46:50,700 --> 00:46:51,850
Like catfish?

573
00:46:52,030 --> 00:46:54,330
I mean, you met this person
online, didn't you?

574
00:46:54,330 --> 00:46:56,800
No, not exactly! It's kinda complicated.

575
00:46:56,800 --> 00:46:58,860
- Could be from a dating site-
- She's NOT!

576
00:46:59,540 --> 00:47:03,610
It's because you've been acting awfully
fishy lately, so we're keeping an eye on you.

577
00:47:03,620 --> 00:47:05,320
I don't need a babysitter, okay!

578
00:47:07,860 --> 00:47:12,980
Taki: The switches stopped, my calls never
connected, and texts never went through.

579
00:47:13,160 --> 00:47:17,690
That's why I decided to
go see Mitsuha in person.

580
00:47:17,690 --> 00:47:20,680
I wanted to see her, but...

581
00:47:22,400 --> 00:47:27,730
-What? You don't know where she is exactly?
The town's landscape is your only clue?

582
00:47:27,900 --> 00:47:29,740
Yeah.

583
00:47:31,530 --> 00:47:35,410
And you can't contact her?
What's that about?

584
00:47:35,620 --> 00:47:38,990
-Where are we?
You're a terrible tour guide-
-'Cause I'm not one!

585
00:47:39,530 --> 00:47:42,570
Oh, well. Guess we'll help you search.

586
00:47:42,570 --> 00:47:47,230
- Aww, it's so cute! Look, Taki!
- Seriously, guys?

587
00:47:47,230 --> 00:47:49,600
Okudera: It moved! Awww!

588
00:48:18,310 --> 00:48:19,410
Taki: This is a lost cause.

589
00:48:19,410 --> 00:48:20,530
- What?!
- What?!

590
00:48:20,530 --> 00:48:23,500
After everything that
we've done for you today?!

591
00:48:26,010 --> 00:48:28,650
You haven't done anything!

592
00:48:31,780 --> 00:48:34,980
- One Takayama Ramen.
- One Takayama Ramen.

593
00:48:34,980 --> 00:48:36,500
I guess I'll have the same.

594
00:48:36,500 --> 00:48:37,840
Sure.

595
00:48:37,840 --> 00:48:40,310
Waitress: Three orders of ramen.
Chef: Got it.

596
00:48:42,200 --> 00:48:46,410
- Think we can make it
back to Tokyo tonight?
- Well, I think we'll be cuttin' it close.

597
00:48:46,410 --> 00:48:47,540
Let me take a look.

598
00:48:47,540 --> 00:48:51,180
- K, thanks.
- Wait, Taki. You sure about that?

599
00:48:52,980 --> 00:48:58,030
Yeah. I kinda feel like maybe I've been
barking up the wrong tree this whole time.

600
00:49:02,020 --> 00:49:05,190
Hey, that's a sketch of Itomori, isn't it?

601
00:49:06,830 --> 00:49:08,690
It's drawn really well.

602
00:49:08,690 --> 00:49:11,070
Come take a look at this, hon!

603
00:49:11,860 --> 00:49:15,040
Yeah, that's Itomori. Takes me back.

604
00:49:15,040 --> 00:49:17,630
My husband was born and raised
there, you know.

605
00:49:17,820 --> 00:49:19,970
Itomori?

606
00:49:21,050 --> 00:49:25,630
Yes, of course! That's the place!
It's nearby, right?

607
00:49:25,780 --> 00:49:27,140
You don't...?

608
00:49:27,140 --> 00:49:29,050
Itomori was...

609
00:49:29,050 --> 00:49:30,990
Itomori...[Gasp]

610
00:49:30,990 --> 00:49:34,640
- But that's where-!
- Wait! Isn't that the
area where that comet-?

611
00:49:35,220 --> 00:49:36,840
Huh?

612
00:49:42,320 --> 00:49:45,330
"Keep Out"

613
00:50:24,000 --> 00:50:25,150
Hey...

614
00:50:25,150 --> 00:50:27,280
Okudera: Is this place really where she's from?

615
00:50:27,280 --> 00:50:31,190
Tsukasa: No way. Taki must have just
confused this with somewhere else.

616
00:50:31,190 --> 00:50:33,300
Taki: No, I didn't.

617
00:50:33,300 --> 00:50:35,420
This was the place.

618
00:50:35,420 --> 00:50:37,730
The schoolyard, these mountains,

619
00:50:37,730 --> 00:50:39,230
even this high school here!

620
00:50:39,230 --> 00:50:40,790
I remember it all!

621
00:50:40,790 --> 00:50:42,740
There's no way you could.

622
00:50:42,740 --> 00:50:46,550
You've gotta know about that
disaster three years ago, right?

623
00:50:46,750 --> 00:50:51,050
- Hundreds of people died.
- They died...

624
00:50:51,050 --> 00:50:53,100
three years ago?

625
00:50:53,100 --> 00:50:55,920
It can't be...

626
00:50:56,120 --> 00:50:57,940
There's no way...

627
00:50:57,940 --> 00:50:59,570
I mean...

628
00:50:59,570 --> 00:51:02,250
I still have the memos she wrote.

629
00:51:19,140 --> 00:51:22,840
They're fading.

630
00:51:30,830 --> 00:51:35,610
Comet Tiamat, with an orbital period
of 1,200 years,

631
00:51:33,330 --> 00:51:37,790
"Itomori, the Town that Vanished"

632
00:51:35,610 --> 00:51:39,780
made a close approach to Earth
three years ago in October.

633
00:51:38,040 --> 00:51:41,790
"Meteor Strikes, Wipes out Town"

634
00:51:39,780 --> 00:51:43,850
Nobody foresaw that its nucleus
would split at its perigee.

635
00:51:43,300 --> 00:51:44,930
"Town Annihilated"

636
00:51:45,050 --> 00:51:46,600
"Over 500 dead or missing"

637
00:51:46,800 --> 00:51:48,180
"Itomori, the Town that Vanished"

638
00:51:49,790 --> 00:51:54,460
A fragment that broke off of it
became a meteor and struck Japan.

639
00:51:53,430 --> 00:51:56,310
"Itomori, comet, damage"

640
00:51:55,710 --> 00:51:59,960
It looks like that day was the
same date as the Autumn Festival.

641
00:52:00,120 --> 00:52:02,490
The point of impact was here.

642
00:52:02,950 --> 00:52:07,890
At 8:42 PM (20:42), it fell right around
where people were gathered for the festival.

643
00:52:10,320 --> 00:52:13,830
"Names of the Victims"

644
00:52:12,070 --> 00:52:14,300
Over 500 died.

645
00:52:14,300 --> 00:52:16,880
It was a third of the town's population,

646
00:52:16,880 --> 00:52:18,880
and now, nobody lives in Itomori anymore.

647
00:52:28,170 --> 00:52:30,200
Teshigawara...

648
00:52:30,200 --> 00:52:31,690
and Sayaka.

649
00:52:32,850 --> 00:52:37,350
"Mitsuha Miyamizu"

650
00:52:36,540 --> 00:52:37,710
That's her?!

651
00:52:37,710 --> 00:52:39,940
You were wrong! You gotta be!

652
00:52:39,940 --> 00:52:43,700
After all,
this girl here died three years ago!

653
00:52:43,700 --> 00:52:48,420
Just... two or three weeks ago,
she said that I'd be able to see the comet.

654
00:52:48,950 --> 00:52:50,670
That means-!

655
00:52:50,670 --> 00:52:55,920
- "You're dreaming right now... aren't you?"
- I...

656
00:52:56,440 --> 00:52:59,640
I...

657
00:52:59,640 --> 00:53:00,640
What...

658
00:53:00,640 --> 00:53:01,370
was I?

659
00:53:15,100 --> 00:53:16,970
Sounds lively over there.

660
00:53:16,970 --> 00:53:19,970
They only have one room left.
I'm really sorry.

661
00:53:19,970 --> 00:53:21,880
It's not a problem.

662
00:53:22,340 --> 00:53:23,600
How's Taki?

663
00:53:23,600 --> 00:53:26,210
He's still reading articles on Itomori.

664
00:53:26,210 --> 00:53:30,890
He's goin' through all those newspapers
and magazines at random. Seems obsessive.

665
00:53:35,290 --> 00:53:38,380
- What is it?
- Oh, sorry. You smoke, huh?

666
00:53:38,690 --> 00:53:42,070
Yeah. I did quit at one point.

667
00:53:43,020 --> 00:53:46,100
What do you think about
what Taki's been saying?

668
00:53:48,820 --> 00:53:51,550
I had feelings for him, y'know.

669
00:53:51,550 --> 00:53:53,780
The way he's been recently.

670
00:53:53,780 --> 00:53:57,750
I mean, he was a nice guy
before, but he's even nicer now.

671
00:53:58,370 --> 00:54:00,770
Kind-of... frantic.

672
00:54:00,770 --> 00:54:02,800
It was cute.

673
00:54:02,800 --> 00:54:07,480
Although, I do think what he's been
telling us is definitely strange-sounding.

674
00:54:09,250 --> 00:54:15,440
But in the end, the fact remains that Taki's met
someone, and that someone is the reason he changed.

675
00:54:15,840 --> 00:54:19,700
That much is for sure.

676
00:54:16,940 --> 00:54:19,850
"Worst-Ever Itomori Comet Disaster"

677
00:54:33,220 --> 00:54:35,720
It was all just a dream.

678
00:54:36,590 --> 00:54:38,590
I recognized the landscape

679
00:54:38,590 --> 00:54:43,110
because I unconsciously remembered
the news from three years ago.

680
00:54:43,960 --> 00:54:46,870
If it's not that, is she... a ghost?

681
00:54:47,260 --> 00:54:48,890
Or...

682
00:54:48,890 --> 00:54:50,780
did I just make it up?

683
00:54:50,780 --> 00:54:52,440
The whole thing?

684
00:54:55,770 --> 00:54:58,300
What was her name?

685
00:54:58,300 --> 00:55:00,300
I can't remember.

686
00:55:02,020 --> 00:55:04,630
Tsukasa said he was gonna
go ahead and take a bath.

687
00:55:04,700 --> 00:55:06,420
Ms. Okudera,

688
00:55:06,420 --> 00:55:07,530
Uh...

689
00:55:07,530 --> 00:55:09,080
I, um...

690
00:55:09,080 --> 00:55:12,590
I realize I've been saying
a lot of strange things.

691
00:55:12,590 --> 00:55:15,100
I'm really sorry, and thank you.

692
00:55:20,000 --> 00:55:21,640
"The Tatara Iron-Making Site"

693
00:55:21,640 --> 00:55:24,510
"The Braided Cords of Itomori"

694
00:55:23,360 --> 00:55:25,810
Braided cords. Pretty.

695
00:55:26,530 --> 00:55:28,540
That band on your wrist.

696
00:55:28,540 --> 00:55:31,490
- That's one, isn't it?
- Hm? Oh.

697
00:55:31,490 --> 00:55:33,230
This thing? Guess so.

698
00:55:33,230 --> 00:55:34,620
Somebody...

699
00:55:34,620 --> 00:55:37,000
Someone gave it to me.

700
00:55:37,000 --> 00:55:40,470
I wear it sometimes as...
kind-of a lucky charm.

701
00:55:42,580 --> 00:55:44,030
Who was it?

702
00:55:46,150 --> 00:55:51,970
- It's late. Why don't you go
down and take a bath, too?
- Sure-wait.

703
00:55:54,300 --> 00:55:57,100
Yeah. Someone who makes these,

704
00:55:57,100 --> 00:55:59,100
they once told me something.

705
00:55:59,100 --> 00:56:02,100
The cords represent the flow of time.

706
00:56:02,100 --> 00:56:03,870
They twist and tangle,

707
00:56:03,870 --> 00:56:05,680
unravel and connect,

708
00:56:05,680 --> 00:56:08,710
and that's what time is.

709
00:56:10,320 --> 00:56:11,690
Maybe if I could-

710
00:56:29,570 --> 00:56:32,200
"Around here?"

711
00:56:37,820 --> 00:56:39,720
Taki...

712
00:56:39,730 --> 00:56:41,700
Distant Voice: Taki.

713
00:56:41,700 --> 00:56:44,710
Taki!

714
00:56:44,710 --> 00:56:46,620
Don't you remember?!

715
00:56:46,620 --> 00:56:49,040
[Gasp]

716
00:57:00,830 --> 00:57:05,840
"I have to go somewhere. Go back to Tokyo
without me. I'll return later. Thanks."

717
00:57:09,110 --> 00:57:10,110
Taki...

718
00:57:34,560 --> 00:57:36,730
Eat this bento up there.

719
00:57:37,720 --> 00:57:41,990
Your drawing of Itomori.
You did a real good job.

720
00:58:19,370 --> 00:58:21,860
-They assemble and take shape,

721
00:58:21,860 --> 00:58:23,600
they twist, tangle,

722
00:58:23,600 --> 00:58:25,280
unravel now and then,

723
00:58:25,280 --> 00:58:26,050
break,

724
00:58:26,050 --> 00:58:27,980
and reconnect.

725
00:58:28,610 --> 00:58:30,490
That's what a union is.

726
00:58:30,490 --> 00:58:32,920
What time is.

727
00:58:43,910 --> 00:58:46,370
There it is.

728
00:58:47,400 --> 00:58:48,990
It's really there!

729
00:58:49,940 --> 00:58:51,080
It wasn't...

730
00:58:51,080 --> 00:58:53,380
a dream.

731
00:59:23,410 --> 00:59:26,990
What lies ahead is the netherworld.

732
00:59:49,470 --> 00:59:51,690
It's still here.

733
00:59:52,800 --> 00:59:57,380
This was Yotsuha's, and this was mine.

734
00:59:59,410 --> 01:00:01,270
This was before the comet.

735
01:00:01,780 --> 01:00:03,980
So when I switched places with her,

736
01:00:04,300 --> 01:00:07,010
it was also three years in the past.

737
01:00:08,250 --> 01:00:12,020
Our times... got tangled somehow.

738
01:00:12,750 --> 01:00:15,580
This is... half of her.

739
01:00:29,850 --> 01:00:30,970
Musubi,

740
01:00:32,220 --> 01:00:36,020
if it's true, and time can be unraveled,

741
01:00:36,020 --> 01:00:39,070
just give me one more chance.

742
01:00:49,290 --> 01:00:50,940
Agh!

743
01:00:51,360 --> 01:00:52,780
[Gasp]

744
01:00:52,780 --> 01:00:55,000
A comet!

745
01:01:01,030 --> 01:01:04,030
ngh! Hh...

746
01:01:48,200 --> 01:01:56,790
[Heartbeat]

747
01:01:56,790 --> 01:02:00,930
- [Crying]
- Your name's going to be...

748
01:02:00,930 --> 01:02:02,180
Mitsuha.

749
01:02:08,670 --> 01:02:11,040
Both of you are my treasures.

750
01:02:11,040 --> 01:02:14,140
You're going to be a big sister!

751
01:02:13,320 --> 01:02:14,790
"Get well soon, Mom!"

752
01:02:16,060 --> 01:02:20,310
I'm so sorry, my dears...

753
01:02:20,770 --> 01:02:23,980
Dad, when is mommy coming home?

754
01:02:24,760 --> 01:02:28,080
- I couldn't help her!
- Get ahold of yourself!

755
01:02:28,080 --> 01:02:31,350
- Who cares about the shrine?!
- But you're in charge now!

756
01:02:31,350 --> 01:02:35,260
- I loved Futaba, not Miyamizu Shrine!
- Get out!

757
01:02:38,550 --> 01:02:40,540
Now listen to me, girls.

758
01:02:40,540 --> 01:02:44,980
Starting today,
you'll be living with grandma.

759
01:02:49,180 --> 01:02:50,430
"Who are you?"

760
01:02:49,220 --> 01:02:51,800
"Who am I?" Who are you?

761
01:02:50,430 --> 01:02:51,680
"Mitsuha"

762
01:02:51,680 --> 01:02:52,780
"Idiot"

763
01:02:51,800 --> 01:02:53,290
Don't be full of yourself!

764
01:02:53,290 --> 01:02:55,380
Like you have a girlfriend!

765
01:02:55,380 --> 01:02:56,800
Must be nice.

766
01:02:56,800 --> 01:02:59,310
They've probably met up about now.

767
01:03:00,480 --> 01:03:01,830
Why am I...?

768
01:03:01,830 --> 01:03:06,090
- I'm going to Tokyo.
- What?! Wait, Sis!

769
01:03:07,540 --> 01:03:09,050
Grandma?

770
01:03:09,050 --> 01:03:12,080
Would you mind doing me a favor?

771
01:03:12,080 --> 01:03:15,100
Oh yeah, the comet.

772
01:03:15,100 --> 01:03:18,170
It'll be at its brightest today, right?

773
01:03:18,170 --> 01:03:20,570
-Mitsuha, don't go there!

774
01:03:21,230 --> 01:03:22,620
Mitsuha!

775
01:03:22,620 --> 01:03:26,070
You've gotta get out of town
before the comet strikes!

776
01:03:26,070 --> 01:03:28,160
[Gasp]

777
01:03:28,160 --> 01:03:30,600
Mitsuha, run!

778
01:03:30,660 --> 01:03:37,340
Mitsuha! Mitsuha! Mitsuha!

779
01:03:42,540 --> 01:03:45,010
[Gasp]

780
01:03:53,860 --> 01:03:55,350
Taki (as Mitsuha): Mitsuha.

781
01:03:55,350 --> 01:03:57,980
She's alive!

782
01:03:58,630 --> 01:04:04,330
[Sobbing]

783
01:04:07,510 --> 01:04:09,580
Let me guess, you're touching your boo-

784
01:04:09,580 --> 01:04:10,670
[Gasp]

785
01:04:10,930 --> 01:04:14,770
[Crying] Her sister!

786
01:04:16,140 --> 01:04:18,330
Yotsuha!

787
01:04:18,330 --> 01:04:19,350
Yotsuha: Ungh!

788
01:04:19,350 --> 01:04:21,670
[Shudder]

789
01:04:21,670 --> 01:04:24,170
I think she's finally lost it.

790
01:04:24,170 --> 01:04:27,540
Just for today,
I-I'm gonna head out first...

791
01:04:27,540 --> 01:04:28,860
She's lost it...

792
01:04:28,860 --> 01:04:30,070
Really lost it...

793
01:04:30,070 --> 01:04:31,410
Totally!

794
01:04:31,410 --> 01:04:32,660
Totally...

795
01:04:32,660 --> 01:04:38,410
-For all you stargazers out there, the comet Tiamat
has been visible to the naked eye for about a week now.

796
01:04:38,410 --> 01:04:44,770
Tonight, it will finally reach its perigee around 7:40 PM (19:40),
and be at its maximum brightness when viewed from the Earth's...

797
01:04:44,770 --> 01:04:47,730
It's tonight! There's still time left!

798
01:04:48,160 --> 01:04:50,220
Mornin', Mitsuha!

799
01:04:50,220 --> 01:04:52,510
What's this?

800
01:04:52,510 --> 01:04:53,850
Hold on...

801
01:04:53,850 --> 01:04:57,690
- You're not Mitsuha, are you?
- W-wait, how did you-?

802
01:04:58,120 --> 01:05:00,170
You already knew?

803
01:05:00,170 --> 01:05:07,200
No, but watching the way you've been
behaving lately stirred some memories up.

804
01:05:07,550 --> 01:05:09,890
When I was a young girl,

805
01:05:09,890 --> 01:05:13,010
I had some pretty strange dreams myself.

806
01:05:13,010 --> 01:05:13,810
Huh?

807
01:05:13,810 --> 01:05:20,710
Though it's been so long, the memories of who I became
in those dreams have pretty much faded at this point.

808
01:05:20,710 --> 01:05:21,940
Faded?

809
01:05:21,960 --> 01:05:27,230
Treasure the experience.
Dreams eventually will fade away.

810
01:05:27,230 --> 01:05:30,050
I went through similar times myself,

811
01:05:30,050 --> 01:05:32,700
and so did your mother.

812
01:05:33,200 --> 01:05:34,310
What if...

813
01:05:34,310 --> 01:05:36,960
all those dreams that
the Miyamizu people had!

814
01:05:36,960 --> 01:05:39,300
It had to do with today!

815
01:05:39,950 --> 01:05:42,720
Grandma, you have to listen to me!

816
01:05:43,040 --> 01:05:44,490
Tonight,

817
01:05:44,490 --> 01:05:46,800
the comet is going to fall on Itomori!

818
01:05:46,800 --> 01:05:49,190
- You're all gonna die!
- Huh?

819
01:05:55,390 --> 01:05:57,390
"Nobody's gonna believe that?"

820
01:05:57,390 --> 01:06:00,340
I didn't expect that out
of Mitsuha's grandma.

821
01:06:00,340 --> 01:06:04,270
It doesn't matter!
There's no way I'm gonna let them all die!

822
01:06:04,820 --> 01:06:06,280
Mitsuha!

823
01:06:06,280 --> 01:06:07,820
What happened... to-?

824
01:06:09,150 --> 01:06:10,550
What'd you-?

825
01:06:10,550 --> 01:06:11,520
Your hair!

826
01:06:11,520 --> 01:06:16,000
-Ugh, the haircut?
Looked better before, huh?
-No, i-i-it's good!

827
01:06:16,000 --> 01:06:20,690
Nevermind that! If we don't do
something about tonight, we'll all die!

828
01:06:22,410 --> 01:06:25,400
It's up to us to save everyone!

829
01:06:29,350 --> 01:06:31,410
Wait, shouldn't you be in school?

830
01:06:31,410 --> 01:06:36,120
Well, we sort-of have to save the
town, or something.

831
01:06:36,120 --> 01:06:37,120
Heh?

832
01:06:37,820 --> 01:06:41,380
- The warning system?
- Yeah, those speakers all over the town.

833
01:06:41,470 --> 01:06:44,890
"Superimposition, frequency"

834
01:06:45,400 --> 01:06:48,280
I get it. It could work!

835
01:06:48,280 --> 01:06:52,540
- Niiiice job, Teshi.
- Hey, I don't think you should
be sittin' so close to me.

836
01:06:52,540 --> 01:06:56,150
- What's wrong. Uh-oh! You shyyy?
- Would you quit it?!

837
01:06:56,150 --> 01:06:58,400
It ain't proper and you know it!

838
01:06:58,400 --> 01:07:00,880
"Club Discontinued - Keep Out"

839
01:06:59,680 --> 01:07:01,830
Taki (as Mitsuha): T-hahahahaha!

840
01:07:01,830 --> 01:07:05,130
Such a gentleman.

841
01:07:06,060 --> 01:07:08,000
I bought all the snacks, guys.

842
01:07:08,000 --> 01:07:10,470
- Here's the change.
- Sorry for the trouble.

843
01:07:10,470 --> 01:07:11,470
I didn't mind.

844
01:07:11,590 --> 01:07:14,660
- We oughta be gettin' paid.
- Quit complaining.

845
01:07:15,500 --> 01:07:17,670
So? Wha'dcha come up with?

846
01:07:17,670 --> 01:07:20,080
Got an evacuation plan?

847
01:07:23,090 --> 01:07:24,610
A- A-

848
01:07:24,610 --> 01:07:26,020
A BOMB?!

849
01:07:26,020 --> 01:07:30,370
Yeah, we have water gel explosives we
use for construction at our storage site.

850
01:07:30,370 --> 01:07:33,010
AND the warning system?

851
01:07:33,360 --> 01:07:37,150
Our startup frequency can hijack the
town's warning system pretty easily,

852
01:07:37,150 --> 01:07:41,340
so we can broadcast an evacuation warning
for the whole town right from school!

853
01:07:41,380 --> 01:07:43,690
Look, we're outside the disaster area here,

854
01:07:43,690 --> 01:07:46,460
so we'll just make an announcement
to evacuate to the school.

855
01:07:46,460 --> 01:07:47,770
It's-

856
01:07:47,770 --> 01:07:50,970
- It's totally a crime!
- You'll be in charge
of the broadcast, Saya.

857
01:07:50,970 --> 01:07:53,460
- Why me?!
- You're in the Broadcast Club.

858
01:07:53,590 --> 01:07:57,250
- And I'll be in charge of the explosives.
- While I go have a word with the mayor.

859
01:07:57,250 --> 01:08:02,140
- Why?
- 'Cause if the evacuation order's not comin' from Town Hall, then nobody's gonna go anyway.

860
01:08:02,140 --> 01:08:05,470
But if I talk to the mayor,
as his daughter, I can convince him.

861
01:08:05,470 --> 01:08:08,120
It's the perfect plan!

862
01:08:08,700 --> 01:08:11,300
Fine, I don't really care
one way or the other.

863
01:08:11,300 --> 01:08:14,190
This is just a theory of yours, right?

864
01:08:14,800 --> 01:08:15,810
Well...

865
01:08:15,810 --> 01:08:21,590
Theories can be based on reality. Like, do you know the
story of how Itomori Lake was formed? It's a crater!

866
01:08:19,750 --> 01:08:23,750
"A meteor crater lake
formed 1,200 years ago."

867
01:08:21,590 --> 01:08:28,090
- That means a meteor hit this area
at least once a thousand years ago!
- Right. That's why-!

868
01:08:28,090 --> 01:08:29,890
Nice one, Teshi!

869
01:08:33,620 --> 01:08:35,520
- Let's go evacuate the town!
- Let's go evacuate the town!

870
01:08:39,700 --> 01:08:42,710
Mitsuha's Father: What on earth
are you talking about?!

871
01:08:43,720 --> 01:08:45,040
Like I said,

872
01:08:45,040 --> 01:08:50,000
-We have to evacuate everyone
in town before tonight or else-
-Enough! Shut up!

873
01:08:54,580 --> 01:08:58,470
"The comet's going to split
in two and strike the town?"

874
01:08:58,020 --> 01:09:01,010
"Itomori Town Hall"

875
01:08:58,470 --> 01:09:01,140
"Over 500 will die?"

876
01:09:01,140 --> 01:09:04,620
How dare you stand there
and spout such nonsense!

877
01:09:05,110 --> 01:09:08,030
If you're serious, you must be sick!

878
01:09:08,030 --> 01:09:12,000
I guess recklessness is a Miyamizu trait.

879
01:09:12,820 --> 01:09:16,450
I'll have a car take you to the
city hospital for an examination.

880
01:09:16,450 --> 01:09:20,380
We will continue this discussion
after you've seen a doctor.

881
01:09:21,820 --> 01:09:23,880
You!

882
01:09:24,570 --> 01:09:28,010
You son of a- !

883
01:09:34,440 --> 01:09:36,000
Mitsuha's Father: Mitsuha...

884
01:09:37,020 --> 01:09:38,390
No...

885
01:09:38,970 --> 01:09:40,410
Wait a minute...

886
01:09:41,520 --> 01:09:43,590
Who are you?

887
01:09:58,000 --> 01:10:01,950
-I'll see you guys at the festival, ba-bye!
-We'll meet ya at the step stone shrine.
Don't be late, k?

888
01:10:01,950 --> 01:10:04,910
- Ba-bye!
- Seeya!
- Later!

889
01:10:06,030 --> 01:10:07,710
You shouldn't go!

890
01:10:07,710 --> 01:10:11,880
-You've got to leave town!
Tell all of your friends!
-What's wrong with you?!

891
01:10:11,880 --> 01:10:15,300
- Mitsuha!
- What was that about?
- Come on, let's go.

892
01:10:15,300 --> 01:10:17,700
What are you doing, huh?

893
01:10:18,060 --> 01:10:20,030
If it was Mitsuha,

894
01:10:20,030 --> 01:10:22,320
would she have been able to convince him?

895
01:10:22,320 --> 01:10:24,190
- Is all this my fault?!
- Huh?!

896
01:10:24,190 --> 01:10:27,930
Yotsuha, promise me that you'll
leave town with grandma before dark!

897
01:10:27,930 --> 01:10:28,570
What?!

898
01:10:28,570 --> 01:10:31,670
- You're gonna die if you stay here!
- What are you talking about?!

899
01:10:31,670 --> 01:10:37,530
And why did you suddenly go to Tokyo yesterday?!
You've been acting really strange lately!

900
01:10:38,300 --> 01:10:42,750
- Went to Tokyo?
- Hey! Mitsuha!

901
01:10:44,700 --> 01:10:46,960
How'd it go with your old man?

902
01:10:48,810 --> 01:10:51,250
Hey, Mitsuha!

903
01:10:51,250 --> 01:10:52,900
What's with your sister?

904
01:10:52,900 --> 01:10:55,280
Don't know.

905
01:11:02,360 --> 01:11:03,510
[Ding]

906
01:11:04,070 --> 01:11:06,410
Could she be over there?

907
01:11:06,580 --> 01:11:08,890
What's that? What's over there?

908
01:11:09,210 --> 01:11:12,030
- Let me use your bike, Teshi.
- Hey.

909
01:11:12,030 --> 01:11:14,040
Mitsuha.

910
01:11:14,350 --> 01:11:16,060
And what do we do?

911
01:11:16,060 --> 01:11:18,200
Get things ready like we planned!

912
01:11:18,200 --> 01:11:20,930
I'm counting on you!

913
01:11:46,360 --> 01:11:49,010
Mitsuha: Oh my gosh! I'm Taki again!

914
01:11:52,090 --> 01:11:54,630
What's Taki doin' out here?

915
01:12:03,710 --> 01:12:05,480
The town!

916
01:12:05,480 --> 01:12:07,370
It's gone!

917
01:12:16,780 --> 01:12:18,000
So...

918
01:12:18,540 --> 01:12:20,000
does that mean...

919
01:12:22,350 --> 01:12:24,910
I... died?!

920
01:12:34,800 --> 01:12:36,710
"Taki."

921
01:12:36,710 --> 01:12:39,020
"Taki!"

922
01:12:40,140 --> 01:12:41,800
"Don't you remember?!"

923
01:12:54,520 --> 01:12:56,550
I'm going to Tokyo for a few hours.

924
01:12:56,550 --> 01:12:58,370
Wha? Right now?

925
01:12:58,370 --> 01:12:59,800
- But why?
- Uh...

926
01:12:59,800 --> 01:13:01,210
For a date.

927
01:13:01,210 --> 01:13:05,320
- You have a boyfriend in Tokyo?!
- I-I didn't say it was a date for me.

928
01:13:06,730 --> 01:13:09,000
"I'll be back tonight."

929
01:13:11,440 --> 01:13:17,000
Mitsuha: If I suddenly show up, will it
be a nuisance or a surprise?

930
01:13:17,000 --> 01:13:20,000
He might not like it if I do.

931
01:13:27,060 --> 01:13:31,370
"The number you are trying to reach
is currently outside the cellular network."

932
01:13:31,370 --> 01:13:34,620
I guess it won't happen, but...

933
01:13:34,620 --> 01:13:36,640
What if it did?

934
01:13:36,640 --> 01:13:38,590
What would I do?

935
01:13:38,590 --> 01:13:40,640
Would I annoy him?

936
01:13:40,330 --> 01:13:43,330
"Tiamat Makes
Closest Approach Tomorrow"

937
01:13:40,640 --> 01:13:44,750
Would it be awkward, or maybe...

938
01:13:44,750 --> 01:13:47,990
he'd be glad to see me.

939
01:13:48,300 --> 01:13:52,590
"The number you are trying to reach
is currently outside the cellular network."

940
01:13:53,350 --> 01:13:55,870
I guess we won't meet.

941
01:13:56,970 --> 01:14:01,860
But... there's one thing I'm certain of.

942
01:14:02,330 --> 01:14:04,520
If we see each other,

943
01:14:04,520 --> 01:14:07,320
We'll definitely know right away...

944
01:14:07,840 --> 01:14:11,530
that you were the one who was in me,

945
01:14:11,530 --> 01:14:14,800
and that I was the one who was in...

946
01:14:14,800 --> 01:14:16,550
- you.
- Sorry!

947
01:14:38,580 --> 01:14:39,640
[Gasp]

948
01:14:47,860 --> 01:14:50,000
'Scuse me.

949
01:15:09,740 --> 01:15:12,000
Taki: Agh!

950
01:15:21,410 --> 01:15:22,630
That time...

951
01:15:22,630 --> 01:15:24,230
three years ago.

952
01:15:24,230 --> 01:15:26,290
Before I even knew you...

953
01:15:29,490 --> 01:15:31,830
Mitsuha: [Whispering] Taki...

954
01:15:31,830 --> 01:15:34,800
Taki?

955
01:15:34,800 --> 01:15:37,010
- Taki!
- Huh?

956
01:15:37,130 --> 01:15:40,000
Uh... It's me!

957
01:15:41,710 --> 01:15:44,410
- Don't you... remember?
- Uh...

958
01:15:45,110 --> 01:15:48,010
Sorry, who are you?

959
01:15:51,610 --> 01:15:53,470
I- I'm sorry.

960
01:15:56,690 --> 01:15:58,000
Ah!

961
01:16:00,740 --> 01:16:03,000
Mitsuha: But, he's Taki!

962
01:16:03,750 --> 01:16:04,960
Taki: What a weird girl.

963
01:16:05,190 --> 01:16:09,070
Train announcer: "Yotsuya. Yotsuya.
Stay clear of the doors."

964
01:16:14,110 --> 01:16:15,620
- Hold on!
- Huh?

965
01:16:15,870 --> 01:16:17,620
- Egh!
- What's your name?

966
01:16:18,410 --> 01:16:20,100
Mitsuha!

967
01:16:20,100 --> 01:16:21,360
My name is...

968
01:16:21,360 --> 01:16:23,480
"Mitsuha!"

969
01:16:28,980 --> 01:16:31,230
Taki (as Mitsuha): Three years ago...

970
01:16:31,230 --> 01:16:33,230
you showed up.

971
01:16:33,230 --> 01:16:37,010
It was... to see me!

972
01:16:47,590 --> 01:16:49,940
Mitsuha (as Taki): Taki.

973
01:16:57,500 --> 01:17:00,360
[Echoing] Mitsuha!

974
01:17:00,360 --> 01:17:02,690
Taki?

975
01:17:16,290 --> 01:17:18,340
Mitsuha!

976
01:17:18,340 --> 01:17:20,500
You're here, right?

977
01:17:20,500 --> 01:17:22,520
Inside my body?

978
01:17:22,520 --> 01:17:24,730
Taki?!

979
01:17:24,730 --> 01:17:27,080
Taki, where are you?!

980
01:17:27,080 --> 01:17:29,250
Taki (as Mitsuha): That was Mitsuha.

981
01:17:29,250 --> 01:17:31,140
I can hear her voice, but...

982
01:17:32,090 --> 01:17:34,850
Taki, where are you?

983
01:17:35,250 --> 01:17:37,200
Taki!!

984
01:17:40,790 --> 01:17:41,930
[Ding]

985
01:17:41,930 --> 01:17:42,940
- Uh!
- Huh?

986
