1063
01:22:20,590 --> 01:22:22,170
Someone precious!

1064
01:22:22,170 --> 01:22:24,600
Someone I don't wanna forget!

1065
01:22:24,600 --> 01:22:26,750
Someone I shouldn't!

1066
01:22:26,750 --> 01:22:28,170
Who was it?

1067
01:22:28,170 --> 01:22:29,750
Who was it?!

1068
01:22:29,750 --> 01:22:30,640
Who?!

1069
01:22:30,890 --> 01:22:31,890
Who?!

1070
01:22:31,890 --> 01:22:34,730
What's your name?!

1071
01:22:48,440 --> 01:22:49,730
Mitsuha: Taki.

1072
01:22:49,730 --> 01:22:50,810
Taki.

1073
01:22:50,810 --> 01:22:52,220
Taki.

1074
01:22:52,220 --> 01:22:53,470
It'll be fine!

1075
01:22:53,470 --> 01:22:54,670
I remember!

1076
01:22:54,670 --> 01:22:56,410
I'll never forget!

1077
01:22:56,410 --> 01:22:57,470
Taki.

1078
01:22:57,590 --> 01:22:58,850
Taki.

1079
01:22:58,850 --> 01:23:00,140
Your name is...

1080
01:23:00,140 --> 01:23:02,990
Taki!

1081
01:23:11,400 --> 01:23:13,400
"Itomori Substation"

1082
01:23:16,370 --> 01:23:17,860
Teshi!

1083
01:23:17,860 --> 01:23:18,860
Mitsuha!

1084
01:23:19,310 --> 01:23:22,680
- Where the heck have you been?
- He said sorry for breakin' your bike.

1085
01:23:22,680 --> 01:23:24,440
Wha? Who did?

1086
01:23:24,440 --> 01:23:26,000
I did!

1087
01:23:26,580 --> 01:23:29,530
You're gonna have to
explain it to me later.

1088
01:23:33,320 --> 01:23:35,310
That thing is gonna fall, right?

1089
01:23:35,310 --> 01:23:38,500
- For real?
- For real. I saw it with my own eyes.

1090
01:23:38,500 --> 01:23:41,310
What? You did, huh?

1091
01:23:41,310 --> 01:23:44,040
Well, I guess it's settled, then.

1092
01:23:44,040 --> 01:23:46,460
We're both officially criminals.

1093
01:23:47,240 --> 01:23:49,240
"Broadcasting Room"

1094
01:23:47,890 --> 01:23:51,260
What?! Do I really have to...?!

1095
01:23:51,260 --> 01:23:55,360
Once the town's power goes out, the emergency
generator should kick in right away.

1096
01:23:55,360 --> 01:23:57,540
Use the broadcast equipment once it does.

1097
01:23:57,540 --> 01:24:00,920
Don't be scared, Saya!
And repeat it as many times as you can!

1098
01:24:00,920 --> 01:24:02,300
Woo-hoo!

1099
01:24:02,300 --> 01:24:07,250
- You can do it!
- Aw, nuts! It's do or die!

1100
01:24:13,090 --> 01:24:16,280
- Shouldn't it be goin' off?
- Hell if I know!

1101
01:24:24,770 --> 01:24:26,850
- Oooh...
- Ha ha!

1102
01:24:27,110 --> 01:24:29,020
- What was that?
- It was pretty loud, too.

1103
01:24:29,020 --> 01:24:30,960
Look over there!

1104
01:24:55,350 --> 01:24:58,990
- Hey look, up there!
- Whoa!

1105
01:25:06,660 --> 01:25:10,050
This is Itomori Town Hall!

1106
01:25:10,050 --> 01:25:15,000
- Reports of an explosion at
the substation are coming in!
- An explosion? Did I hear that right?

1107
01:25:15,000 --> 01:25:19,560
Wildfires are possible,
as well as the threat of more explosions!

1108
01:25:19,560 --> 01:25:25,840
Residents in the followin' areas, please
evacuate to Itomori High School immediately.

1109
01:25:26,320 --> 01:25:28,550
Kadoiri District.

1110
01:25:28,550 --> 01:25:31,160
- Sakagami District!
- Honey, we should go.

1111
01:25:31,160 --> 01:25:34,610
The broadcast isn't coming from us?
Well, who the hell is it, then?

1112
01:25:34,610 --> 01:25:36,730
Miyamori District.

1113
01:25:37,390 --> 01:25:39,910
Oyazawa District.

1114
01:25:39,990 --> 01:25:42,180
Let's go, Mitsuha!

1115
01:25:43,600 --> 01:25:45,010
Teshi!

1116
01:25:51,150 --> 01:25:56,590
- Everyone, run! There's a wildfire!
- Wildfire, please run!

1117
01:25:56,590 --> 01:26:01,440
- Get outta here! Run, there's a fire!
- It's not safe here! Please, evacuate!

1118
01:26:01,630 --> 01:26:04,090
It's not workin',
we're runnin' out of time!

1119
01:26:04,090 --> 01:26:06,600
- Mitsuha!
- [Sobbing]

1120
01:26:06,600 --> 01:26:08,000
What's wrong?

1121
01:26:08,500 --> 01:26:10,570
What is it...?

1122
01:26:10,570 --> 01:26:13,980
I can't remember what his name is anymore!

1123
01:26:15,300 --> 01:26:19,160
What is with you?!
You're the one who started all of this!

1124
01:26:19,160 --> 01:26:22,640
We can't evacuate everyone
without firefighters!

1125
01:26:22,640 --> 01:26:25,900
Get goin'! You gotta convince your old man!

1126
01:26:33,210 --> 01:26:37,100
Everybody, get to the high school! HURRY!

1127
01:26:39,030 --> 01:26:40,990
Oh, it's Mitsuha.

1128
01:26:43,760 --> 01:26:48,700
-Why would terrorists attack way out here?
What is Chubu Electric saying?
-They're still checking.

1129
01:26:48,700 --> 01:26:51,210
Any update? No wildfires yet?

1130
01:26:51,210 --> 01:26:53,300
You sure? Got it.

1131
01:26:54,460 --> 01:26:58,440
Make them stop this broadcast immediately!
Haven't you located its source yet?

1132
01:26:58,440 --> 01:27:01,390
Mayor, the Takayama sensor
station just called!

1133
01:27:02,490 --> 01:27:04,040
From the high school?

1134
01:27:04,180 --> 01:27:09,780
Once again, residents in the following
areas, please evacuate to Itomori High...

1135
01:27:09,780 --> 01:27:12,660
- Ah!
- What are you doing?! Turn that off!

1136
01:27:15,200 --> 01:27:17,600
- They got Saya!
- Oh no.

1137
01:27:20,900 --> 01:27:23,780
What were you thinking, Natori?! I swear!

1138
01:27:27,270 --> 01:27:30,780
This is Itomori Town Hall.

1139
01:27:30,780 --> 01:27:35,310
We are currently confirming
the reports of the accident.

1140
01:27:35,490 --> 01:27:42,180
- We instruct all residents to remain calm and stay where they are until further notice.
- I guess... we have to stay put?

1141
01:27:42,430 --> 01:27:44,700
- What is goin' on?
- So stay on standby.

1142
01:27:45,500 --> 01:27:50,360
Come on! They said everyone should evacuate!
The high school's the evacuation center!

1143
01:27:50,360 --> 01:27:52,500
-Katsuhiko!

1144
01:27:54,760 --> 01:27:55,740
Tell me...

1145
01:27:55,740 --> 01:27:58,510
What do you think you're doing?!

1146
01:28:00,700 --> 01:28:02,490
Sorry, Mitsuha.

1147
01:28:03,480 --> 01:28:05,440
This is the end.

1148
01:28:05,840 --> 01:28:07,020
[Gasp]

1149
01:28:07,020 --> 01:28:08,520
Oh, my God!

1150
01:28:08,520 --> 01:28:11,330
It's actually splittin' apart!

1151
01:28:17,710 --> 01:28:23,890
Look at that! The comet has split into two large
parts and meteors are now falling to Earth!

1152
01:28:24,140 --> 01:28:28,380
- Uh, I don't believe anyone
could have predicted this.
- Either way, we have
quite the mystical view here.

1153
01:28:28,380 --> 01:28:31,870
-So, what does the comet's
nucleus splitting mean for us?

1154
01:28:31,870 --> 01:28:37,690
-The comet's not within the Roche limit, so the nucleus
itself must've had a structural weakness for this to happen.

1155
01:28:37,690 --> 01:28:42,520
-Comet Shoemaker-Levy 9 broke apart
and collided with Jupiter in 1994.

1156
01:28:43,060 --> 01:28:45,220
- There were at least 21 fragments...
- I'm going outside to take a look.

1157
01:28:45,220 --> 01:28:48,650
- The fragments will likely burn up
well before reaching the ground.
- Does it pose a danger?

1158
01:28:48,650 --> 01:28:53,020
-Probability of a meteor actually landing
on a populated area is quite small.

1159
01:28:53,020 --> 01:28:54,650
-never foresaw this development.

1160
01:28:54,650 --> 01:28:58,770
- To predict the trajectory...
- As we stand here witnessing
this spectacle,

1161
01:28:58,770 --> 01:29:00,270
unassisted...

1162
01:29:00,270 --> 01:29:01,590
and with our bare eyes,

1163
01:29:01,590 --> 01:29:06,970
it strikes me that living in such an age
has never felt more fortunate than now.

1164
01:29:09,580 --> 01:29:10,700
Mitsuha: Hey...

1165
01:29:11,210 --> 01:29:12,310
Who...

1166
01:29:12,310 --> 01:29:14,000
are you?

1167
01:29:16,830 --> 01:29:18,200
Who?

1168
01:29:18,560 --> 01:29:20,240
Who?

1169
01:29:20,330 --> 01:29:22,260
Who is he?

1170
01:29:22,260 --> 01:29:24,030
Someone precious.

1171
01:29:24,030 --> 01:29:26,020
Someone I shouldn't forget!

1172
01:29:26,020 --> 01:29:28,740
Someone I didn't want to!

1173
01:29:28,740 --> 01:29:30,430
Who?

1174
01:29:30,430 --> 01:29:31,510
Who?!

1175
01:29:31,510 --> 01:29:33,410
Who are you?!

1176
01:29:33,410 --> 01:29:36,150
What's your name?!

1177
01:29:41,010 --> 01:29:42,460
Oh no!

1178
01:29:42,520 --> 01:29:43,880
Ah! Argh!

1179
01:29:47,660 --> 01:29:48,780
Ungh!

1180
01:30:01,840 --> 01:30:04,410
-"So that we don't forget
things when we wake up..."

1181
01:30:04,410 --> 01:30:06,990
"Let's write down our names."

1182
01:30:15,110 --> 01:30:18,510
"I love you"

1183
01:30:33,580 --> 01:30:35,160
Writing this...

1184
01:30:35,160 --> 01:30:36,790
doesn't help!

1185
01:30:36,790 --> 01:30:39,090
I won't know your name...

1186
01:30:39,090 --> 01:30:41,130
[Crying]

1187
01:30:52,080 --> 01:30:54,280
Dad!

1188
01:30:54,830 --> 01:30:56,900
- Mitsuha.
- There you are!

1189
01:30:56,900 --> 01:30:59,110
Don't tell me you're back!

1190
01:30:59,110 --> 01:31:01,000
Ah...

1191
01:31:03,000 --> 01:31:06,090
-"It was almost like seeing
something out of a dream."

1192
01:31:06,510 --> 01:31:08,340
"Nothing more or less..."

1193
01:31:08,340 --> 01:31:10,700
"than a breathtaking view."

1194
01:31:10,700 --> 01:31:15,110
Words like "tomorrow"
or "future" or "fate",

1195
01:31:15,110 --> 01:31:18,910
no matter how far they extend their hands,

1196
01:31:18,910 --> 01:31:22,720
we breathe, we dream, we raise our love

1197
01:31:22,720 --> 01:31:26,860
in a timeless land
that is far out of reach.

1198
01:31:26,860 --> 01:31:30,530
Even the second, hour hands of the clock.

1199
01:31:30,530 --> 01:31:34,550
They look at us sideways
as they tick and tock.

1200
01:31:34,550 --> 01:31:39,410
How I hope to have
forever to spend this life,

1201
01:31:39,410 --> 01:31:41,830
no- all future lives

1202
01:31:41,830 --> 01:31:49,630
right here in this world with you!

1203
01:32:42,390 --> 01:32:43,850
Taki: Huh?

1204
01:32:44,310 --> 01:32:45,880
Why am I here?

1205
01:32:47,170 --> 01:32:49,980
What am I... doing?

1206
01:33:07,480 --> 01:33:08,570
[Gasp]

1207
01:33:08,570 --> 01:33:09,680
U-uh!

1208
01:33:14,310 --> 01:33:18,010
Train Announcer: "The doors are closing.
Please be careful."

1209
01:33:20,600 --> 01:33:23,400
Taki: I'm always searching for something.

1210
01:33:23,400 --> 01:33:27,030
This... feeling has consumed me...

1211
01:33:27,030 --> 01:33:28,990
for some time.

1212
01:33:30,290 --> 01:33:32,350
The reason I applied for this position-

1213
01:33:32,350 --> 01:33:33,890
The landscapes people live in-

1214
01:33:33,890 --> 01:33:35,840
To build a city's landscape-

1215
01:33:35,840 --> 01:33:38,800
Even Tokyo. It might vanish too one day.

1216
01:33:38,800 --> 01:33:43,210
And so, I wanna make landscapes
that- how should I put this?

1217
01:33:43,210 --> 01:33:46,700
That can continue to warm peoples' hearts.

1218
01:33:46,700 --> 01:33:48,340
[Sigh]

1219
01:33:48,340 --> 01:33:50,650
Takagi: That bad? How many does that make it?

1220
01:33:50,650 --> 01:33:53,400
Taki: I've stopped counting.
Tsukasa: Doesn't sound too promising.

1221
01:33:53,400 --> 01:33:55,990
- Who asked you?
- That suit could be the problem.

1222
01:33:55,990 --> 01:33:57,760
-It looks just like yours!

1223
01:33:57,760 --> 01:34:01,170
- Well, I have two offers.
- I have eight myself.

1224
01:34:03,580 --> 01:34:07,400
"LINE: You have a new message."

1225
01:34:06,290 --> 01:34:08,380
Taki: Is what I'm searching for...

1226
01:34:08,380 --> 01:34:09,880
someone?

1227
01:34:09,880 --> 01:34:11,370
Or somewhere?

1228
01:34:12,110 --> 01:34:15,390
Or am I just searching
for the right job?

1229
01:34:15,390 --> 01:34:17,320
I don't even really know.

1230
01:34:18,030 --> 01:34:19,220
Oh!

1231
01:34:19,220 --> 01:34:23,100
- You're job hunting, huh?
- I haven't had much luck, though.

1232
01:34:23,100 --> 01:34:27,950
- Hey, maybe it's the suit
that's killing your chances.
- Uh-does it really look that bad on me?

1233
01:34:32,250 --> 01:34:34,850
-So, why the sudden call today?

1234
01:34:34,850 --> 01:34:40,010
-I was in the area for work and I figured
it had been a while since I saw your face.

1235
01:34:39,430 --> 01:34:42,920
"8 years since the comet disaster"

1236
01:34:42,130 --> 01:34:46,070
Okudera: Remember that one time when we
went all the way to Itomori?

1237
01:34:46,070 --> 01:34:49,350
You were still in high school back
then, so it was...

1238
01:34:49,350 --> 01:34:52,580
- Heh. Five years ago.
- That long?

1239
01:34:53,160 --> 01:34:54,530
